onto'' series. The project features two collaborations, one with Mansa and the other with [[Lil Tjay]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hypebeast.com/2020/4/tory-lanez-the-new-toronto-3-album-stream|title=Tory Lanez Is a Free Man With Latest Mixtape 'The New Toronto 3'|website=Hypebeast|last=Caraan|first=Sophie|date=April 9, 2020|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref> ''The New Toronto 3'' follows four months after Lanez's prior release ''[[Chixtape 5]]'', released as an album in a series of prior mixtapes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rap-up.com/2020/04/09/tory-lanez-new-toronto-3-tracklist/|title=Tory Lanez Reveals 'The New Toronto 3' Tracklist|work=[[Rap-Up]]|date=April 9, 2020|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref> It was supported by three singles: \"Broke in a Minute\", \"Do the Most\" and \"Who Needs Love\".\n\n==Background==\n''The New Toronto 3'' is the final release of Lanez's five-album contract with [[Interscope Records]]. The project was intended to be released in March 2020, but was delayed due to Lanez's label issues, which he has aired through social media, writing on [[Instagram]] that he has had to \"dumb down [his] creativity\" and that his prior release, ''Chixtape 5,'' was the \"closest thing [he's] been able to give [...] that had somewhat of the quality\" he intends his future music to have.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://thesource.com/2020/04/09/tory-lanez-ready-to-drop-the-new-toronto-3-and-become-independent-artist/|title=Tory Lanez Ready to Drop The New Toronto 3 and Become Independent Artist|work=[[The Source]]|last=White|first=Roman|date=April 9, 2020|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Singles==\nThree singles were released prior to the album, including the songs \"Broke in a Minute\", \"Who Needs Love\" and \"Do the Most\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2020/04/tory-lanez-new-toronto-3-stream|title=Tory Lanez Drops 'The New Toronto 3' Mixtape f/ Lil Tjay and Mansa|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|last=Espinoza|first=Joshua|date=April 10, 2020|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| [[Album of the Year (website)|AOTY]] = 75/100<ref name=\"AOTY\">{{cite web|url=https://www.albumoftheyear.org/album/229217-tory-lanez-the-new-toronto-3.php|title= The New Toronto 3: Reviews|website=[[Album of the Year (website)|Album of the Year]]|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev1 = ''[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]''\n| rev1score = 7/10<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clashmusic.com/reviews/tory-lanez-the-new-toronto-3|title=Tory Lanez: The New Toronto 3 review \u2013 An imposing return from the Toronto star...|author=Aaron Bishop|work=[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]|date=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[Exclaim!]]''\n| rev2score = 8/10<ref name=\"Exclaim\">{{cite web|last=Mullin|first=Kyle|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/tory_lanez_the_new_toronto_3_mixtape_album_review|title=Tory Lanez Owns His Flaws on 'The New Toronto 3'|work=[[Exclaim!]]|date=April 15, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[NME]]''\n| rev3score ={{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"NME\">{{cite web|last=Pearce|first=Sheldon|url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/tory-lanez-the-new-toronto-3-review-2644620|title=Tory Lanez \u2013 \u2018The New Toronto 3\u2019 review: more depth and introspection than he\u2019s given credit for|website=[[NME]]|date=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\nAt [[Album of the Year (website)|Album of the Year]], which assigns a [[Weighted arithmetic mean|weighted mean]] rating out of 100 to reviews from mainstream publications, the album received a score of 75, based on 2 reviews.<ref name=\"AOTY\"/>\n\n==Commercial performance==\n''The New Toronto 3'' debuted at number two on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with 64,000 [[album-equivalent unit]]s (including 5,000 copies in pure album sales) in its first week. It is Lanez' fith US top-five album on that chart.<ref name=\"BB200\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9361577/the-weeknd-after-hours-billboard-200-albums-chart-month-no-1|title=The Weeknd Makes It a Month at No. 1 on Billboard 200 Albums Chart|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref> The album also accumulated a total of 76.1 million on-demand streams of the album\u2019s songs.<ref name=\"BB200\"/>\n\nIn his home country of Canada, the album debuted at number one on the [[Canadian Albums Chart]], earning a total number of 10 million on-demand streams in its first week, becoming his second number-one debut in the country.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.fyimusicnews.ca/articles/2020/04/19/tory-lanez-has-every-reason-be-smiling-week|title=Tory Lanez Has Every Reason To Be Smiling This Week|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n| headline = ''The New Toronto 3'' track listing\n| total_length = 44:14\n| title1 = Pricey & Spicy\n| writer1 = {{hlist|[[Tory Lanez|Daystar Peterson]]|Daniel Gonzalez}}\n| extra1 = {{hlist|Play Picasso|[[Tory Lanez]]}}\n| length1 = 2:31\n| title2 = The Coldest Playboy\n| writer2 = {{hlist|Peterson|Isom Green III|Gonzalez}}\n| extra2 = {{hlist|9three|Play Picasso|Lanez}}\n| length2 = 2:00\n| title3 = Stupid Again\n| writer3 = {{hlist|Peterson|Jonathan Priester}}\n| extra3 = {{hlist|Supah Mario|Nik Dean}}\n| length3 = 2:54\n| title4 = 10 Fucks\n| note4 = with Mansa\n| writer4 = {{hlist|Peterson|Mansa Evans|Ben Unfug|Sterling Purdy|Gonzalez}}\n| extra4 = {{hlist|B&N|HAYES|Mansa|Play Picasso|Lanez}}\n| length4 = 2:49\n| title5 = Dope Boy's Diary\n| writer5 = {{hlist|Peterson|[[Don Cannon|Donald Cannon]]}}\n| extra5 = {{hlist|[[Don Cannon]]|Sean Momberger}}\n| length5 = 3:04\n| title6 = Accidents Happen\n| note6 = with [[Lil Tjay]]\n| writer6 = {{hlist|Peterson|[[Lil Tjay|Tione Merritt]]|[[C-Sick|Charles Dumazer]]|Gonzalez}}\n| extra6 = {{hlist|[[C-Sick]]|Play Picasso|Lanez}}\n| length6 = 3:24\n| title7 = Broke in a Minute\n| writer7 = {